<recipe>
    <name>Persian Chicken With Rice (Zereshk Polo ba Morgh)</name>
    <indexCharacter>P</indexCharacter>
    <notes></notes>
    <servings>0</servings>
    <instructions>1. Chop the onion
2. Pour enough oil into a large, flat pan to saut√© the onion pieces
3. Remove the skin from the chicken pieces
4. Wash the chicken pieces
5. Place the chicken pieces on top of the onion pieces, bone sides down
6. Cover the pan and cook for about five minutes
7. Sprinkle a little salt on the chicken 
8. Sprinkle the chicken liberally with turmeric, cinnamon and Persian spice mix
9. Turn the chicken pieces over
10. Sprinkle the salt and spices on the bottom of the chicken
11. Put the lid on the pan and cook for 30 minutes
12. Wash the rice three times to get rid of extra starch
13. Add enough water to cover the rice and cook for 10 minutes
14. Soak barberry fruit in water for 15 minutes
15. Once the rice is cooked, drain it with a colander
16. Put a small amount of saffron into a small mug
17. Add approximately 1/2 cup of boiling water
18. Add 2-3 tablespoons of butter to the hot water
19. Shake the colander to get extra water out of the rice
20. Pour rice back into its cooking vessel
21. Pour the saffron butter over the rice, saving 1/3 of it for the chicken and the barberry
22. Steam the rice for 15 minutes
23. After 30 minutes, turn the chicken pieces over and cook for another 15 minutes
24. Drizzle half the leftover saffron butter on the chicken pieces, then put the lid back on the pan
25. Fish barberry fruit from the top of the water into a colander, checking carefully for thorns or small stones
26. Wash the barberry in the colander, still checking for impurities 
27. Put two tablespoons of sugar into a small pan
28. Add some boiling water to dissolve the sugar 
29. Swish the pan around to dissolve the sugar
30. Add the barberry and let it simmer for a couple of minutes (uncovered)
31. Add the rest of the saffron butter to the barberry, then stir to mix it in
32. Plate rice (she spread across the whole plate)
33. Plate barberry as a small stripe across the middle of the plate
34. Plate pistachios on one side of the barberry and chicken on the other
35. Spread some of the cooking juices from the chicken on top of the chicken</instructions>
